name: setupData
getTotalParkings
query:
from(bucket: "Projeto")
  |> range(start: 0)
  |> filter(fn: (r) => r["_measurement"] == "parkingData")
  |> group()
  |> count()
  |> map(fn: (r) => ({ r with _value: float(v: r._value) / 7.0 }))
  |> yield(name: "divided_count")

name: getTotalValue
query:
from(bucket: "Projeto")
 |> range(start: 0) // This sets the range to all available data. You might want to adjust this for specific timeframes.
 |> filter(fn: (r) => r._field == "valor")
 |> group()
 |> sum()

name: convertData
getAgeDistribution
query:
from(bucket: "Projeto")
  |> range(start: 0)
  |> filter(fn: (r) => r["_measurement"] == "parkingData")
  |> filter(fn: (r) => r["_field"] == "age")
  |> map(fn: (r) => ({ r with count_per_record: 1 }))
  |> group(columns: ["_value"])
  |> sum(column: "count_per_record")
  |> yield(name: "age_counts")

name: roundValue
func:
msg.payload = msg.payload[0]._value.toFixed(2);
return msg;

name: getParkingsByDay
query:
from(bucket: "Projeto")
  |> range(start: -7d)
  |> filter(fn: (r) => r["_measurement"] == "parkingData")
  |> aggregateWindow(every: 1d, fn: count, createEmpty: false)
  |> group(columns: ["_time", "_measurement"])
  |> sum(column: "_value")
  |> map(fn: (r) => ({ r with _value: float(v: r._value) / 7.0 }))
  |> yield(name: "TotalParkingCountPerDay")
